answerText: Mosquito Coast [or Miskito Coast][10] The Mosquito Coast lies mostly in this country, whose large namesake lake would be a central part of a proposed waterway connecting the Atlantic to the Pacific.

question: Question: This region was not colonized by the British or Americans due to the Clayton-Bulwer Treaty. For 10 points each: [10] Name this region of Central America bordering the Caribbean Sea, that includes the city of Bluefields. Although this region's name refers to a group of natives, it is often spelled after a certain insect.
